2018-10-22 15:32:25,407 p=10530 u=junior |  ERROR! Syntax Error while loading YAML.
  found character that cannot start any token

The error appears to have been in '/home/junior/SIC/TEST/get-facts.yml': line 11, column 1, but may
be elsewhere in the file depending on the exact syntax problem.

The offending line appears to be:

    - ntc_get_facts:
	   platform: "cisco_ios_ssh"
^ here
There appears to be a tab character at the start of the line.

YAML does not use tabs for formatting. Tabs should be replaced with spaces.

For example:
    - name: update tooling
      vars:
        version: 1.2.3
#    ^--- there is a tab there.

Should be written as:
    - name: update tooling
      vars:
        version: 1.2.3
# ^--- all spaces here.

2018-10-22 20:15:25,000 p=15792 u=junior |  ERROR! Syntax Error while loading YAML.
  did not find expected '-' indicator

The error appears to have been in '/home/junior/SIC/TEST/get_ip_fact.yml': line 30, column 5, but may
be elsewhere in the file depending on the exact syntax problem.

The offending line appears to be:

#   - debug: var={{ intf_ip | to_nice_yaml }}
    - debug: var={{ result }}
    ^ here
We could be wrong, but this one looks like it might be an issue with
missing quotes.  Always quote template expression brackets when they
start a value. For instance:

    with_items:
      - {{ foo }}

Should be written as:

    with_items:
      - "{{ foo }}"

There appears to be a tab character at the start of the line.

YAML does not use tabs for formatting. Tabs should be replaced with spaces.

For example:
    - name: update tooling
      vars:
        version: 1.2.3
#    ^--- there is a tab there.

Should be written as:
    - name: update tooling
      vars:
        version: 1.2.3
# ^--- all spaces here.
We could be wrong, but this one looks like it might be an issue with
missing quotes.  Always quote template expression brackets when they
start a value. For instance:

    with_items:
      - {{ foo }}

Should be written as:

    with_items:
      - "{{ foo }}"
